Lookup the ant &lt;batchtest&gt; and &lt;junitreport&gt;. 

I was using something like this:
&lt;target name=&quot;run-test&quot;&gt;	
	&lt;junit printsummary=&quot;false&quot;
errorProperty=&quot;test.failed&quot;
failureProperty=&quot;test.failed&quot;&gt;
		&lt;classpath&gt;
			&lt;path refid=&quot;some.classpath&quot;/&gt;
		&lt;/classpath&gt;
		&lt;formatter type=&quot;brief&quot; usefile=&quot;false&quot;/&gt;
		&lt;formatter type=&quot;xml&quot; /&gt;				
		&lt;batchtest fork=&quot;true&quot; todir=&quot;${test.result}&quot;&gt;
			&lt;fileset dir=&quot;${build.dir}&quot;
includes=&quot;**/*Test.class&quot;/&gt;
		&lt;/batchtest&gt;
	&lt;/junit&gt;

	&lt;junitreport todir=&quot;${test.result}&quot;&gt;
		&lt;fileset dir=&quot;${basedir}&quot;&gt;
			&lt;include name=&quot;**/*TEST*.xml&quot;/&gt;	
		&lt;/fileset&gt;
		&lt;report format=&quot;noframes&quot; todir=&quot;${test.result}&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;/junitreport&gt;

	&lt;fail message=&quot;Test failed - aborting build&quot;
if=&quot;test.failed&quot;/&gt;
&lt;/target&gt;





